Many of the plain linear 7805s I've tested act like a shunt regulator at 5V... you'll statically lose some power into them by back-feeding them, but I wouldn't be worried about damaging them.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Thu Dec 04, 2014 9:44 pm</p><hr />
